        <section id="headers_whitelist.p.keep_header">
            <title><varname>keep_header</varname> (string)</title>
            <para>
                Additional header names to keep. The value is parsed as a
                semicolon-separated list of names (for example,
                <quote>X-Foo;X-Bar</quote>).
            </para>
            <para>
                This parameter can be set multiple times; values are accumulated.
            </para>
            <para><emphasis>Default value is empty.</emphasis></para>
            <example>
                <title>Set <varname>keep_header</varname> parameter</title>
                <programlisting format="linespecific">
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_header", "X-Foo;X-Bar")
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_header", "Contact")
...
</programlisting>
            </example>
        </section>

        <section id="headers_whitelist.p.keep_header_case_sensitive">
            <title><varname>keep_header_case_sensitive</varname> (int)</title>
            <para>
                Controls case sensitivity when matching header names from
                <varname>keep_header</varname> against SIP headers.
            </para>
            <para>
                Value <quote>1</quote> enables case-sensitive matching;
                value <quote>0</quote> enables case-insensitive matching.
            </para>
            <para>
                When JSON profiles are used, this value is applied per profile
                from each profile object.
            </para>
            <para><emphasis>Default value is 1 (case-sensitive).</emphasis></para>
            <example>
                <title>Set <varname>keep_header_case_sensitive</varname> parameter</title>
                <programlisting format="linespecific">
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "keep_header_case_sensitive", 0)
...
</programlisting>
            </example>
        </section>

        <section id="headers_whitelist.p.params_json_file">
            <title><varname>params_json_file</varname> (string)</title>
            <para>
                Path to a JSON file containing an array of profile objects.
                Each object must define <varname>profile_name</varname>.
            </para>
            <para>
                Unnamed profile objects are skipped and a warning is logged:
                <quote>profile[id] without name will be skipped due to unnamed</quote>.
            </para>
            <para>
                If this parameter is not set, an internal default profile
                named <quote>default</quote> is created from module parameters.
            </para>
            <para>
                If this parameter is set and script function
                <function moreinfo="none">whitelist_headers()</function> is
                used (without explicit profile), the first profile from the
                loaded array (index 0) is used.
            </para>
            <example>
                <title>Set <varname>params_json_file</varname> parameter</title>
                <programlisting format="linespecific">
...
modparam("headers_whitelist", "params_json_file",
    "/etc/kamailio/headers_whitelist_profiles.json")
...
</programlisting>
            </example>
            <example>
                <title>JSON profiles file structure</title>
                <programlisting format="linespecific"><![CDATA[
...
[
    {
        "profile_name": "edge_inbound",
        "keep_header_case_sensitive": 0,
        "keep_header": [
            "X-Trace-ID",
            "X-Request-ID",
            "P-Charging-Vector"
        ]
    },
    {
        "profile_name": "trunk_minimal",
        "keep_described_rfc3261": 0,
        "keep_path_rfc3327": 0,
        "keep_diversion_rfc5806": 0,
        "keep_rpid": 0,
        "keep_reason_rfc3326": 0,
        "keep_header_case_sensitive": 1,
        "keep_header": [
            "X-Custom-Trunk"
        ]
    }
]
...
]]></programlisting>
            </example>
        </section>
    </section>

    <section>
        <title>Functions</title>
        <section id="headers_whitelist.f.whitelist_headers">
            <title>
                <function moreinfo="none">whitelist_headers()</function>
            </title>
            <para>
                Removes all SIP headers except the ones allowed by RFC 3261 and
                enabled by module parameters.
            </para>
            <para>
                The function marks headers for deletion using lumps. In normal
                request/reply routing, changes are applied automatically.
            </para>
            <para>
                To force immediate effect during configuration processing,
                call <function moreinfo="none">msg_apply_changes()</function>
                afterwards.
            </para>
            <para>
                It can be used in REQUEST_ROUTE, ONREPLY_ROUTE,
                FAILURE_ROUTE, and BRANCH_ROUTE.
            </para>
            <para>
                When JSON profiles are enabled via
                <varname>params_json_file</varname>, this function logs a
                warning and applies the first profile from loaded profile
                array (index 0).
            </para>
            <example>
                <title><function>whitelist_headers</function> usage</title>
                <programlisting format="linespecific">
...
whitelist_headers();
...
</programlisting>
            </example>
        </section>

        <section id="headers_whitelist.f.whitelist_headers_with_profile">
            <title>
                <function moreinfo="none">whitelist_headers_with_profile(profile)</function>
            </title>
            <para>
                Same behavior as
                <function moreinfo="none">whitelist_headers()</function>,
                but uses a specific whitelist profile by name.
            </para>
            <para>
                The profile must exist in loaded profiles (from JSON or default profile).
            </para>
            <example>
                <title><function>whitelist_headers_with_profile</function> usage</title>
                <programlisting format="linespecific">
...
whitelist_headers_with_profile("default");
...
</programlisting>
            </example>
        </section>
    </section>

